{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cc9ac66e-d7eb-423f-8003-d02c9f9e6dfe","content":"The environment has `dotnet` but not `dotnet-dump`. I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory either. Here's how to proceed:\n\n### Analyzing your .dmp file\n\n**1. Install `dotnet-dump`** (the primary .NET dump analysis tool):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n```\n\n**2. Analyze the dump:**\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your/file.dmp\n```\n\n**3. Key commands inside the analyzer:**\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show the last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Stack for a specific thread |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n\n### Typical workflow to find crash root cause:\n1. Run `pe` to check for an unhandled exception\n2. Run `threads` to find threads with exceptions\n3. Run `clrstack` on the faulting thread to see where it crashed\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` here and analyze your file? If so, please share the path to your `.dmp` file (or upload it to this session).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7e1e9b14-785f-4d88-9877-80ca6416c514","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The environment has `dotnet` but not `dotnet-dump`. Let me check if we can install it, and also check for the .dmp file location.","outputTokens":378,"requestId":"2C45:9B616:1803977:1AF6663:69F94EE3"},"id":"c5ec5a15-9896-4454-b6b2-57dde0d044fa","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:59:09.902Z","parentId":"64b4649c-1843-4740-9473-c7c3cb9c7902"}
